      "writtenOn": "2019-03-14T05:14:21Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I initially did \"None indicates the value should be removed\".\n\nThen I went to write https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/infra/infra/+/1522435 and realized I intuitively used None there as \"do not override default\". So I went back and changed it here to mean \"do not override default\".\n\nI later also realized this is more consistent with how we merge lists (there\u0027s no way to delete an item from a list provided via defaults), and with how we merge scalar values (\u0027None\u0027 means \"use default\"). I think adding an ability to \"unset\" defaults will be a complication.",
      "parentUuid": "d231f2d0_823e8094",
      "revId": "9c0f9e54df0187e62c50a239241c29230cf8c81a",
